<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06157e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06157e">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06157e"> 157(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> prosecute trespassers</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[from the FIFTH PETITION]</font> The forgiveness of God is a full and free forgiveness; He has promised to forgive all our trespasses. &ldquo;God was in Christ reconciling the world unto Himself, not imputing their trespasses unto them.&rdquo; He has said, &ldquo;If ye forgive not men their trespasses, <mark>neither will your Father forgive your trespasses</mark>.&rdquo; <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 46</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
